honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class BluetoothConfiguration_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.BluetoothConfiguration_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class BluetoothConfiguration_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Bluetooth Configuration data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1Bluetooth Device Name
    2Bluetooth Service Name
    3Discoverable
    4Connectable
    5Bondable
    6Authentication Type
    7Encryption
    8PassKey
    9Inactive Disconnect TIme
    10Power Down Time
    11Bluetooth Device Address
    12Bluetooth Enable
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • BluetoothConfiguration_DPL

        public BluetoothConfiguration_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
